  Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc 
will not pay bonuses for last year to as many as a third of
employees in its global banking and markets division, Mark Kleinman wrote in his column in the Financial Times.  That would be a far higher proportion than the banking
industry average, Kleinman said, without saying where he got the
information. Kleinman is City editor of Sky News.  To contact the reporter on this story:
